workflow.name: PartnerStack/Impact ‚Üí WooCommerce product creation with GPT-4 & AI images
workflow.description:
# üöÄ PartnerStack/Impact ‚Üí WooCommerce (AI-Powered Product Automation)

**Turn affiliate programs into fully published WooCommerce products‚Äîon autopilot.**
This n8n template pulls offers from PartnerStack/Impact (or your own links), generates SEO copy and images with AI, and publishes **External** products to WordPress/WooCommerce‚Äîhands-free.

---

## üéØ What This Automation Does

* ‚è∞ **Runs on a schedule** (e.g., daily at 10:00 or every 3 days)
* üìÑ **Reads rows from Google Sheets** (your affiliate product registry)
* üîó **Inserts your affiliate link** (PartnerStack/Impact/CJ or manual)
* üåê **Fetches product/landing page** and parses key details
* ü§ñ **Uses AI** to create product title, short & long HTML description
* üñºÔ∏è **Creates a product image** from an AI image prompt
* üóÇÔ∏è **Uploads media to WordPress**, sets alt/title/caption
* üõí **Creates a WooCommerce External product** via REST API
* üè∑Ô∏è **Applies category by ID** and sets the featured image
* ‚úÖ **Marks the row as published** to avoid duplicates
* üßØ **Graceful error handling** (failed fetches are flagged & skipped next run)

üõí **Output of Wordpress Website Product:**
[![AI Affiliate Product Automation](https://pics.paypal.com/00/p/NTk4ZDFiMzQtNmI4OS00NGU3LTgyNmEtZTE4MzgwOWVjYzJj/image_3.PNG)](https://brenttechnologies.com/)



---

## üßë‚Äçüè´ Step-by-Step Video Tutorial

üé• **Watch the implementation tutorial:**
[![AI Affiliate Product Automation](https://img.youtube.com/vi/Pifwn32vlQk/hqdefault.jpg)](https://youtu.be/Pifwn32vlQk)

üìå *Live demo: schedule, sheet ‚Üí product, AI copy/image, REST publish.*
---

## üåê Useful Links

* üîó **Start with n8n (Cloud or Self-hosted):**
  üëâ [https://n8n.io](https://n8n.syncbricks.com)  |  Guide: [https://syncbricks.com/self-hosting-n8n-on-ubuntu-24-04-a-step-by-step-guide/](https://syncbricks.com/self-hosting-n8n-on-ubuntu-24-04-a-step-by-step-guide/)

* üß† **OpenAI API (text + image):**
  üëâ [https://platform.openai.com/docs](https://platform.openai.com/docs)
* ü§ù **PartnerStack:**
  üëâ [https://partnerstack.com](https://try.partnerstack.com/cg3ksh2ipx4f)
* üìÑ **Google Sheets API:**
  üëâ [https://developers.google.com/sheets/api](https://developers.google.com/sheets/api)

---

## üõ† Prerequisites

* ‚úÖ n8n (self-hosted or Cloud)
* ‚úÖ WordPress + WooCommerce with REST API enabled
* ‚úÖ WordPress Application Password / API credential with media & products scope
* ‚úÖ OpenAI (or your preferred AI) API key
* ‚úÖ Google Sheet with minimum columns:

  * `AdvertiserIdandCompaignID` (unique key)
  * `AdvertiserUrl` (merchant/product URL)
  * `TrackingLink` (your affiliate URL)
  * `Brand`
  * `partner_status` (e.g., ‚ÄúActive‚Äù)
  * `product_published` (Yes/blank)
  * `error` (Yes/blank)

---

## üìã Step-by-Step Implementation

### 1Ô∏è‚É£ Scheduling & Intake

* Add a **Schedule Trigger** (daily, every 3 days, or your cadence).
* **Google Sheets ‚Üí Read**: pull rows from your ‚Äúimpact/partnerstack‚Äù tab.
* **Filter** rows: `partner_status = Active` AND `product_published != Yes` AND `error != Yes`.
* **Limit** to 1 per run (safe scaling). Increase later if needed.

### 2Ô∏è‚É£ Product Discovery & Parsing

* **HTTP Request** the `AdvertiserUrl` to fetch the landing/product page.
* Parse title/meta/summary; continue on error and flag failures (so runs don‚Äôt break).

### 3Ô∏è‚É£ AI Content Generation

* **Agent 1 ‚Äì Basics:** Product Name, Short Description, Category ID mapping (match your Woo categories).
* **Agent 2 ‚Äì Long Form:** SEO-ready **HTML** description (H2/H3, bullets, features, benefits, target users, technical highlights).
* **Agent 3 ‚Äì Image Prompt:** Generate a clean product-hero prompt; then **AI Image** generation.

### 4Ô∏è‚É£ Media Handling

* **Upload media** to WordPress (`/wp/v2/media`) with title/alt/caption and proper content-type.
* Capture the **media ID** for the next step.

### 5Ô∏è‚É£ WooCommerce Product Creation

* **Create product** via `POST /wc/v3/products` with:

  * `type: "external"`
  * `name`, `short_description`, `description`
  * `external_url: TrackingLink`
  * `button_text: "Sign Up"` (or ‚ÄúBuy Now‚Äù / ‚ÄúGet It Now‚Äù)
  * `status: "publish"` (or ‚Äúdraft‚Äù if you want manual review)
* **Attach featured image** with the uploaded `media ID`.
* **Set categories** by **ID** (ensure your mapping is correct).

### 6Ô∏è‚É£ Post-Publish Updates

* **Update the Google Sheet row** using the unique key (`AdvertiserIdandCompaignID`):

  * `product_published = Yes`
  * Clear/reset any transient error flags.

### 7Ô∏è‚É£ Error Handling & Idempotency

* If fetch fails (e.g., Cloudflare/Turnstile), mark `error = Yes` and **skip** that row next run.
* Filter excludes `error = Yes` and already-published rows‚Äîno accidental duplicates.

---

## üí∞ Optional Monetization & Distribution

* **Blog & Social:** Add branches to generate a blog article, LinkedIn/Twitter posts from the same product data.
* **Video:** Create a short promo video (Sora/Gen-AI) and auto-schedule to TikTok/YouTube/Instagram.
* **Email:** Trigger a campaign (e.g., Brevo/Mailchimp) for new products added this week.

---

## üí° Advanced Customizations

* **Draft workflow:** publish products as `draft` for human QA.
* **Category Mapper:** expand the category ID table to fit your Woo taxonomy.
* **Image sizing:** add an optional resize/optimize node before upload.
* **Batching:** remove the Limit node to publish multiple products per run (respect rate limits).
* **Per-brand theming:** vary prompts (tone/structure) based on Brand column.

---

## üß∞ Troubleshooting

| Issue                         | Fix                                                                                      |
| ----------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| WordPress 401/403             | Re-create Application Password; ensure correct base URL & permalinks                     |
| Image upload fails            | Check content-type & binary upload settings; verify max upload size on server            |
| Product lacks image/category  | Confirm media ID capture & category ID mapping                                           |
| Duplicate items               | Ensure `product_published` is set to `Yes` after success; keep Limit node during testing |
| Fetch errors on merchant site | Keep ‚Äúcontinue on error‚Äù; route to set `error = Yes`, then review manually               |

---

## üôå Why Use This Template

* ‚è±Ô∏è **Saves hours** of manual listing work
* üìà **SEO-consistent** product pages every time
* üß† **AI-quality copy & images** with your tone
* üîó **Affiliate link everywhere**, fully tracked
* üõ†Ô∏è **Extensible** to blog, social, video, and email

---

## üöÄ Get Started Now

Import the template ‚Üí Connect credentials ‚Üí Point to your Sheet ‚Üí Run once ‚Üí Enable schedule.
Need help or a DFY build? **SyncBricks** can implement and customize this for your stack.

üëâ **Amjid Ali** ‚Äî [https://linkedin.com/in/amjidali](https://linkedin.com/in/amjidali)
üåê **Website** ‚Äî [https://amjidali.com](https://amjidali.com) | [https://syncbricks.com.au](https://syncbricks.com.au)
‚ñ∂Ô∏è **YouTube** ‚Äî [https://youtube.com/@syncbricks](https://youtube.com/@syncbricks)

---

**Knowledge Base:** `woocommerce-rest`, `partnerstack`, `impact`, `affiliate-automation`, `openai`, `n8n`, `google-sheets`, `content-generation`, `image-generation`, `wordpress-api`, `creator-hub`

The Edit Image node allows you to manipulate and edit images. Use this node when you want to:

- Blur an image
- Add a border to an image
- Create a new image
- Crop an image
- Composite an image on top of another
- Draw on an image
- Get information about the image
- Rotate an image
- Change the size of an image
- Shear an image along the X or Y axis
- Add text to the image

data.details: The Code node allows you to execute JavaScript in your workflow.

The Filter node can be used to filter items based on a condition. If the condition is met, the item will be passed on to the next node. If the condition is not met, the item will be omitted. Conditions can be combined together by AND(meet all conditions), or OR(meet at least one condition).
